School children on their way to school were injured when they were involved in a collision in the taxi they were travelling in, on the corner of Trafford Rd and Hillclimb Road in Westmead Pinetown, just after 7.30am this morning.    ” Paramedics arrived on the scene to find chaos. A taxi carrying school children to school collided in a T Bone format. Immediately more ambulances were dispatched to assist with the multiple children injured. Once stabilised on the scene a total of 21 children were transported to various hospitals for the further care that they required,” said Garrith Jamieson, managing director of Rescue Care. He said that at this stage the events leading up to the collision is unknown however SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further.